subject: p12963531
Findings: The lung volumes have decreased. Signs of chronic interstitial fluid overload. Marked increase of the cardiac silhouette that is now moderately to severely increased. A central venous access line for dialysis has been placed over the right, the tip of the line projects over the right atrium. Mild bilateral pleural effusions. No hilar or mediastinal lymphadenopathy. No pneumonia. No lung nodules or masses.
